                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While in beta I bought one of each horse and tested them out, and also tested the SK AA horse (same horse cast by the ornate chain bridle).
<br />

<br />
I timed a long run in a straight line with a stopwatch and did a /loc at the beginning and end and then did the math. I tested the following:
<br />

<br />
1.00 - base run speed
<br />

<br />
1.07 - rope
<br />
1.43 - leather
<br />
1.78 - silk
<br />
2.14 - chain
<br />
2.50 - ornate chain
<br />

<br />
1.30 - run3
<br />
1.40 - run4
<br />
1.50 - run5
<br />

<br />
some things to compare to:
<br />
1.35 - jboots
<br />
1.45 - scaled wolf
<br />
1.55 - SoW cast by a level 50+
<br />
1.60 - SoE
<br />
1.62 - share great wolf cast by lv 54+ druid, works with perm illusion
<br />
